content.text:
The VD4DOTS operand assignments are DIFFERENT between the bias and no-bias variants. The bias variant (which passes) has:
```
V0 = V16*V20, V1 = V17*V20, V2 = V18*V20, V3 = V19*V20  // lhs0 * rhs{0-3}
V4 = V16*V21, V5 = V17*V21, ...                            // lhs1 * rhs{0-3}
```

But the no-bias variant has:
```
V0 = V16*V20, V1 = V16*V21, V2 = V16*V22, V3 = V16*V23  // rhs0 * lhs{0-3}
V4 = V17*V20, V5 = V17*V21, ...                            // rhs1 * lhs{0-3}
```

The no-bias variant has the 4x4 accumulator matrix TRANSPOSED! V0-V3 should be lhs0 * rhs{0-3}, but the no-bias version has rhs0 * lhs{0-3}. The VREDSUM + VSLIDEUP packing then packs the wrong values.

This is the bug - the subagent transposed the accumulator assignment for the no-bias variants. Let me fix all 7 failing files.

